com.plexobject.rx

Interface Observable<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - type of subscription data
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ObservableDelegate, ObservableImpl, ObservableNever

    public interface Observable<T>
    The Observable interface defines common methods of reactive extensions, which are implemented in separate class. This is main interface that user interacts with when creating Observable objects.

      • subscribe

        Subscription subscribe(java.util.function.Consumer<T> onNext,
                       java.util.function.Consumer<java.lang.Throwable> onError,
                       OnCompletion onCompletion)
        This method subscribes given consumer and starts pushing the data. By default, data is pushed asynchronously using thread-pool scheduler.
        Parameters:
        onNext - - consumer function that is called to consume the data
        onError - - consumer function that is called for notifying an error
        onCompletion - - function that is invoked when all data is pushed successfully. This will not be called when an error occurs or when user unsubscribes using dispose method of subscription.
        Returns:
        subscription handle that can be used for unsubscribing

      • subscribe

        Subscription subscribe(java.util.function.Consumer<T> onNext,
                       java.util.function.Consumer<java.lang.Throwable> onError)
        This method subscribes given consumer and starts pushing the data. By default, data is pushed asynchronously using thread-pool scheduler. Note: This method doesn't take onCompletion function so user will not be notified when all data is processed, which is not a problems for most cases.
        Parameters:
        onNext - - consumer function that is called to consume the data
        onError - - consumer function that is called for notifying an error
        Returns:
        subscription handle that can be used for unsubscribing
